The paper proposes a deep neural network for structured time series (STS) classification, which involves modeling interweaved spatiotemporal dependency. The proposed architecture is a convolutional neural network (CNN) that is highly modularized and scalable, making it easy to be adapted to specific tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
